	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That wouldn't make any sense to me.
<br />
<br />As it stands all binary loading console emulators rely on hacks (databases or use a ROM's internal header) when they should all have some sort of external board type identifier. In most cases, consoles allow the cartridge to decode ROM and other stuff in multiple ways, for accuracy this is important to emulate because there is more to cartridges than just a ROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
